HEADWORD: Wen
<hw>Wen</hw> <pr>(w⟦ecr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>wenn</ets>; akin to D. <ets>wen</ets>, LG. <ets>wenne</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An indolent, encysted tumor of the skin;
especially, a sebaceous cyst.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

