==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Wen
<hw>Wen</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>. <ety>[AS. <ets>w⟦emac⟧n</ets>.]</ety>
<def>One of the runes (<?/) adopted into the Anglo-Saxon, or Old
English, alphabet. It had the value of modern English <it>w</it>, and
was replaced from about <sc>a. d.</sc> 1280 at first by <it>uu</it>,
later by <it>w.</it></def></p>

<p><ent>Wynd</ent>⟦br⟧
